# SETU General Coding Standards

## Core Principles
- Functional components ONLY. Class components are forbidden.
- All new files must be `.tsx` or `.ts`. No new `.js` files.
- DRY: extract shared logic into `src/hooks` or `src/Utils`.

## Naming Conventions
- **Components/Screens**: PascalCase ‚Üí `UserProfile.tsx`, `DashboardScreen.tsx`
- **Functions/Variables**: camelCase ‚Üí `fetchUserData`, `isLoggedIn`
- **Constants**: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE ‚Üí `API_BASE_URL`, `MAX_RETRY_COUNT`
- **Interfaces/Types**: PascalCase ‚Üí `User`, `ApiResponse`
- **Feature folders**: camelCase ‚Üí `auth/`, `userProfile/`
- **Component folders**: PascalCase ‚Üí `Button/`, `Header/`

## Directory Structure
```
src/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ features/       Redux slices (authSlice.ts, authAPI.ts, selectors.ts)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Screens/        Screen components grouped by feature
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Components/     Reusable UI atoms/molecules
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ hooks/          Custom React hooks
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ services/       API service functions
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Utils/          Helper/utility functions
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Constants/      Theme, colors, config constants
```

## State Management
- Use Redux Toolkit for global state; `useState` for UI-only state.
- Slices live in `src/features/<feature>/`.
- Always use `useSelector` and `useDispatch` hooks.
